As of 2018, the University of Chicago Economics Department has been awarded 13 Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences (laureates were affiliated with the department when receiving the prizes) since the prize was first awarded in 1969. In addition, as of October 2018, 32 out of the total 81 Nobel laureates in Economics have been affiliated with the university as alumni, faculty members or researchers.[4] However, not all members of the department belong to the Chicago school of economics.
